Our family of four, including two young children, was facing an immigration crisis when we contacted the Garfield Law Group. After years of living in the United States, we found ourselves in removal proceedings because of bad advice by unethical lawyers in the past. The Garfield Law Group took our case on and their efforts have allowed our family to remain legally in the US with work permits and hope for the future. In that process, it became evident that this firm is well respected by the department of Justice and in the community as a whole. In performing their job, their attorneys traveled to meet personally with the President of the Korean American Association, our church leaders, and Senator Warner’s office. They fought tirelessly for our family, and their amazing efforts led to success on our case. We cannot stress how competent and caring all their staffs was in preparing our case. They worked miracles as a team of dedicated advocates and continue to extend our legal status free of charge. They are honest attorneys who are fierce and caring advocates. 





