Mr. Garfield and his associate, Jane Park, personally came to my church to meet with me to obtain letters of support from me and other members of our congregation. They kept me apprised of developments on the case, and they informed me that their efforts were successful. I was also aware that Mr. Garfield and two of his Korean associates met the president of the Korean American Association in person to advocate for his client. I was very impressed by their dedication and work product. I was also impressed by their character- Mr. Garfield waived much of the legal fee for his services when it became clear that his client was unable to pay. His entire family was saved by that office 





